{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779178131738,"sessionID":"ses_1c0bd0875ffeDBfk5LNf5rH20A","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_00_BOJdX4D9BCmKhUVbqMMs7020","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude-project/nestfind/design/DOMAIN_RESEARCH.md","content":"# Domain Research — NestFind\n\n**Generated:** 2026-05-19\n**Source:** Phase 2.5 — Domain & Reference Research\n**Purpose:** Identify standard UI patterns and essential sections from top rental property listing platforms before Design Guide generation.\n\n---\n\n## Industry\n\n**Domain:** Real Estate / Rental Property Listings\n\nNestFind operates in the digital rental marketplace vertical — a subset of PropTech (Property Technology) focused exclusively on long-term residential rentals (as opposed to short-term/vacation rentals or property sales). The platform connects renters with available properties through search, discovery, detail views, favorites, and inquiry submission.\n\n**Market Context:**\n- The US online rental market is dominated by Zillow Rentals, Apartments.com, and Realtor.com Rentals\n- Mobile-first search behavior is standard — renters browse on mobile, apply on desktop\n- Key differentiator for newer entrants: streamlined UX, fewer ads, verified listings, built-in application/inquiry flows\n- Map-based search and card-based results are industry-standard UI patterns\n\n---\n\n## Competitors\n\n### Competitor 1: Zillow Rentals (zillow.com/rentals)\n\n**Type:** Full rental marketplace (listings + application management)\n**USP:** Largest inventory, end-to-end renter lifecycle (search → apply → pay rent)\n\n**Landing Page Patterns:**\n- Hero section with large search bar (location input + submit) and tagline \"Zillions of apartments. Ready when you are.\"\n- Feature highlight cards: \"A variety of filters and a large network of rentals\", \"A central Renter Hub\", \"1 fee, 1 form for 30 days\"\n- \"Looking for something specific?\" section with quick-filter chips: Pet-friendly, Apartments, Rentals with parking\n- \"Apply without all the paperwork\" section explaining the application process\n- \"Paying rent online with Zillow is easy\" — ancillary service promotion\n- Budget calculator CTA\n- Blog/resources section: \"Let's find what you're looking for\" with renter guide, budget tool, payment setup\n- Mobile app download promotion\n- Standard footer with About, News, Research, Careers, Help, Legal\n\n**Search/Listing Page Patterns:**\n- Split view: Map on left/right (toggleable), card list on opposite side\n- Filter panel: Price range (min-max), Beds & Baths (min dropdowns), Property Type (multiselect), + More Filters\n- \"Save search\" button prominently placed\n- Property cards: Thumbnail image, price (prominent, large font), address (street + city/state), bed/bath counts, square footage, \"Contact\" or \"Apply\" CTA\n- Cards show heart/favorite icon for saved properties\n- Empty state: \"We could not find any matching results\" with search tips (widen area, reduce filters)\n- Pagination OR infinite scroll\n\n**Detail Page Patterns:**\n- Photo gallery with arrow navigation (carousel or grid)\n- Price, address, key stats (beds, baths, sqft) in header\n- Tabs/sections: Overview, Facts & Features, Schools, Nearby\n- Description (free text)\n- Amenities list with icons\n- Google Map embed with pin\n- Sidebar: Request Tour / Apply / Contact buttons\n- Favorite toggle (heart icon)\n\n**Renter Hub (Dashboard):**\n- Sidebar nav: Search, Saved Searches, Favorites, Messages, Applications, Payments\n- Central dashboard showing recent activity, application statuses\n- \"Your search\" section: active searches with new listing counts\n\n---\n\n### Competitor 2: Apartments.com\n\n**Type:** Rental aggregator with heavy advertising model\n**USP:** Massive inventory, neighborhood guides, 3D tours\n\n**Landing Page Patterns:**\n- Prominent search bar with city/address input\n- \"Popular Searches\" links to major cities\n- Featured neighborhoods/properties\n- Rental tools: Rent calculator, moving center, neighborhood guides\n- \"Find Apartments by State\" directory grid\n\n**Search/Listing Page Patterns:**\n- Filter-heavy sidebar: Price, Beds, Baths, Property Type, Amenities (checkboxes), Pet Policy, Transit Score, Rating\n- Sort options: Best Match, Price (Low to High), Price (High to Low), Most Recent\n- Property cards: Photo, price, address, bed/bath, sqft, \"Available Now\" badge, rating stars\n- Map/list toggle view\n- \"Save\" button per card\n\n**Detail Page Patterns:**\n- Large photo gallery with thumbnail strip\n- Floor plan section (image uploads)\n- Amenities grid with checkmarks\n- Map with nearby points of interest (transit, restaurants, schools)\n- Contact sidebar: Phone, Email, Schedule Tour, Apply Online\n- Price history and availability timeline\n\n**Admin/Manager Dashboard (Apartments.com Manager):**\n- Property portfolio overview\n- Listing performance stats (views, leads, inquiries)\n- Lead/inquiry inbox with statuses (New, Contacted, Tour Scheduled)\n- Property listing editor (photos, description, pricing, availability)\n\n---\n\n### Competitor 3: Airbnb (airbnb.com)\n\n**Type:** Short-term rental marketplace\n**USP:** Best-in-class UX, immersive design, host/guest marketplace\n\n**Landing Page Patterns:**\n- Category bar (horizontal scroll chips): Rooms, Mansions, Amazing pools, Cabins, etc.\n- Card grid with large photos, location name, distance, dates, price per night\n- Each card: Carousel of photos, heart (wishlist) button, location, host type, rating, price\n- Search: \"Where\", \"Check in / Check out\" (date picker), \"Who\" (guests selector)\n- \"Inspiration for your next trip\" sections (themed, curated)\n\n**Detail Page Patterns:**\n- Full-width immersive photo gallery with \"Show all photos\" button\n- Title, rating, location, host info in header\n- Sectioned below: Description, What this place offers (amenities with icons), Where you'll sleep (bedroom breakdown), Map, Host info, Things to know (house rules)\n- Right sidebar: Price, date picker, guest selector, \"Reserve\" CTA, total calculation\n- Wishlist/save functionality (heart icon)\n\n**Key Design Lessons:**\n- Immersive, photo-first design\n- Card carousels on search results pages\n- Sectioned, scannable detail pages\n- Sticky booking/reserve sidebar (or bottom bar on mobile)\n- Trust-building elements: host profiles, reviews, verified badges\n\n---\n\n### Competitor 4: Rentable (rentable.co)\n\n**Type:** Rental marketplace with verified listings focus\n**USP:** Human-verified listings, budget calculator, mobile-first\n\n**Landing Page Patterns:**\n- Hero: \"Every Apartment Near You, In One Place\" + city search input\n- Listing count prominently displayed: \"Browse 10,377,478 apartments\"\n- Grid of popular cities with images\n- Grid of \"Apartments for Rent Near College Campuses\"\n- Testimonials and press mentions (Curbed, NBC Today)\n- Mobile app promotion with ratings (4.7 Apple, 3.6 Google Play)\n- Rent affordability calculator CTA\n- \"Real Apartments, Verified by Real People\" trust section\n- \"What is Rentable?\" about section\n- \"Advertising a Property?\" partner CTA\n- Trusted by: Forbes, MarketWatch, CNBC, Realtor.com, Washington Post logos\n\n**Key Design Lessons:**\n- Social proof sections (press mentions, trust logos, ratings)\n- City/campus browse grids for SEO and discovery\n- Clear value proposition: \"Every Apartment Near You, In One Place\"\n- Strong mobile-first design\n\n---\n\n### Competitor 5: HotPads (hotpads.com)\n\n**Type:** Map-centric rental search (owned by Zillow Group)\n**USP:** Map-first browsing experience with polygon search\n\n**Landing Page Patterns:**\n- Minimal: search + city links\n- No landing \"page\" — immediately drops users into map search\n\n**Search/Listing Page Patterns:**\n- Full-screen map as primary interface\n- Listing cards overlay on top of map\n- Polygon search (draw area on map)\n- Filter bar: Price, Beds, Property Type, More\n- Color-coded map pins by price tier\n- \"My HotPads\" section: Saved searches, saved listings\n\n**Key Design Lessons:**\n- Map as the primary interface (alternative to card-first approach)\n- Minimal design with high information density on map\n\n---\n\n## Reference UI Patterns\n\n### Pattern 1: Property Search Card\n\n**Present in 100% of competitors.** The standard rental property card contains:\n\n| Element | Typical Size/Position | Prevalence |\n|---------|----------------------|------------|\n| Primary photo (thumbnail) | Top, ~280-340px width, 16:9 or 4:3 ratio | 100% |\n| Price | Large, bold, top-right or bottom-left of photo | 100% |\n| Address/Location | Below photo, primary text | 100% |\n| Bed/Bath Count | Below photo, secondary text (e.g., \"2 bd | 1 ba\") | 100% |\n| Square Footage | Below photo, secondary text | 80% |\n| Property Type Badge | On photo overlay (e.g., \"Apartment\", \"Condo\") | 60% |\n| Favorite/Heart Toggle | Top-right corner of card or photo | 80% |\n| \"New\" or \"Available Now\" Badge | On photo overlay | 50% |\n| Rating Stars | Below photo (if reviews available) | 30% |\n| Photo Count | On photo (e.g., \"1/12\" or \"📷 12\") | 70% |\n| \"Contact\" / \"Apply\" CTA | Bottom of card or hover overlay | 60% |\n\n### Pattern 2: Search Filter Panel\n\n**Present in 100% of competitors.** Standard filter hierarchy:\n\n1. **Location** (text input, autocomplete) — always first\n2. **Price Range** (min-max sliders or inputs) — always present\n3. **Bedrooms** (dropdown: Studio, 1+, 2+, 3+, 4+) — always present\n4. **Property Type** (checkboxes: Apartment, House, Condo, Townhouse, Studio) — always present\n5. **Bathrooms** (dropdown: 1+, 1.5+, 2+, 3+) — present in ~80%\n6. **Amenities** (checkboxes: In-unit laundry, Parking, Pet-friendly, AC, Gym, Pool, etc.) — present in ~90%\n7. **Square Footage** (range) — present in ~50%\n8. **Move-in Date** (date picker) — present in ~30%\n9. **Sort** (Best Match, Price Low/High, Newest, Rating) — always present\n10. **\"Save Search\"** button — present in ~70%\n\n### Pattern 3: Photo Gallery (Detail Page)\n\n**Present in 100% of competitors.** Standard patterns:\n\n- **Hero Gallery:** Large featured image with left/right arrows for navigation\n- **Thumbnail Strip:** Row of smaller thumbnails below hero for quick selection\n- **\"View All Photos\" Button:** Opens full-screen lightbox gallery\n- **Photo Count Badge:** e.g., \"1/12\" or \"Show all 12 photos\"\n- **Floor Plan Section:** Separate from photo gallery, often with interactive zoom\n- **Virtual Tour / 3D Tour Link:** Increasingly common (Apartments.com, Zillow)\n\n### Pattern 4: Map Integration\n\n**Present in 95% of competitors.**\n\n- **Embedded Map (Detail Page):** Google Maps iframe with property pin marker; often shows nearby points of interest (transit, schools, restaurants)\n- **Map/Split View (Search Page):** Left panel = card list, right panel = full map; pins update as map pans; drawn area search\n- **Map Pin Design:** Custom marker with price overlay (Zillow), color-coded by price tier (HotPads)\n\n### Pattern 5: Favorites / Saved Properties\n\n**Present in 90% of competitors.**\n\n- Heart icon toggle on property cards and detail page header\n- \"Saved\" or \"Favorites\" page: grid/list of favorited properties\n- Requires authentication (guest users prompted to sign in)\n- Often named \"Saved Homes,\" \"Favorites,\" or \"Saved Properties\"\n- May show count badge in navigation (Zillow: \"Favorites (3)\")\n\n### Pattern 6: Inquiry / Contact Form\n\n**Present in 100% of competitors.** Standard fields: Name, Email, Phone (optional), Message. Submitted to property manager. Typically a modal or sidebar form.\n\n### Pattern 7: Admin Dashboard (Property Management)\n\n**Based on Behance/Dribbble research of property management dashboard designs (~20 analyzed projects):**\n\nStandard dashboard elements:\n- **Sidebar Navigation:** Dashboard, Properties, Inquiries/Messages, Users, Settings, Reports\n- **Top Bar:** Search, Notifications bell, User avatar + dropdown\n- **Overview Stats Cards:** Total Properties, Active Listings, Total Inquiries, Pending Responses, Total Users — displayed as 4-6 metric cards with icon, value, label, trend indicator\n- **Recent Activity Feed:** Timeline of recent inquiries, new user registrations, listing changes\n- **Properties Table:** Columns: Photo (40px thumb), Title, Type, Price, Status (Active/Archived/Draft), Bed/Bath, Date Added, Actions (Edit, Delete, View). With search, filter, sort, pagination.\n- **Inquiry Table:** Columns: Name, Email, Property, Date, Status (New/Read/Responded), Actions (View, Reply, Mark Read)\n- **Users Table:** Renter list with Name, Email, Join Date, Status (Active/Suspended), Actions\n- **Property Editor:** Form with sections: Basic Info, Location/Address, Pricing, Details (beds, baths, sqft, type), Amenities (checkboxes grouped by category), Photos (multi-upload with drag-drop, reorder, preview), Floor Plan upload. Submit/Cancel buttons.\n- **Inquiry Detail/Response View:** Original inquiry message + reply textarea + Mark as Read/Responded status change + Send Reply button\n\n---\n\n## Page-type Conventions\n\n### Landing Page\n\n**Standard Sections (present in 80%+ of competitors):**\n\n| # | Section | Purpose | Prevalence | NestFind Applicability |\n|---|---------|---------|------------|------------------------|\n| 1 | **Navigation Bar** | Logo, nav links, Sign In / Join CTAs | 100% | Required |\n| 2 | **Hero + Search** | Primary search input (city/address) + value prop tagline + CTA | 100% | Required — NestFind's primary entry point |\n| 3 | **Popular Cities / Quick Links** | Grid of city images linking to pre-filtered searches | 80% | Recommended for SEO and discovery |\n| 4 | **How It Works** | 3-step diagram explaining search → find → apply | 70% | Recommended for first-time users |\n| 5 | **Featured Properties** | Carousel or grid of curated listings | 60% | Optional — depends on having listings to feature |\n| 6 | **Value Props / Features** | Icon + text cards explaining platform benefits | 90% | Required |\n| 7 | **Trust / Social Proof** | Testimonials, press logos, review ratings, user counts | 80% | Recommended for credibility |\n| 8 | **Budget Calculator CTA** | \"How much rent can I afford?\" tool link | 40% | Differentiator opportunity |\n| 9 | **Mobile App Promotion** | App store badges, phone mockup, QR code | 50% | Optional (web-first) |\n| 10 | **For Property Managers** | CTA to list properties or advertise | 60% | Important if NestFind has property manager acquisition |\n| 11 | **Footer** | About, Contact, Terms, Privacy, Social links | 100% | Required |\n\n**Key Takeaway:** The hero + search bar is the single most important element. Every rental platform's landing page centers around the search input. Secondary sections build trust and explain value.\n\n### Dashboard (Renter Hub)\n\n**Standard Elements (based on Zillow Renter Hub + design patterns):**\n\n| # | Element | Purpose | Prevalence |\n|---|---------|---------|------------|\n| 1 | **Saved Searches** | Quick access to active searches with new listing counts | 80% |\n| 2 | **Favorites Grid** | Preview of saved properties with quick remove | 70% |\n| 3 | **Messages/Inquiries Inbox** | List of sent inquiries with response statuses | 60% |\n| 4 | **Application Status** | Track submitted applications | 50% |\n| 5 | **Recommended Properties** | Algorithmic suggestions based on saved searches | 50% |\n\n**NestFind Renter Dashboard should include:** Saved Properties (favorites), Active Inquiries (sent messages), Saved Searches (optional), Account Settings link.\n\n### Dashboard (Admin)\n\n**Standard Elements (based on Behance/Dribbble analysis):**\n\n| # | Element | Purpose | Prevalence |\n|---|---------|---------|------------|\n| 1 | **Stats Overview Cards** | Total Properties, Active/Archived, Total Inquiries, Total Users | 100% |\n| 2 | **Recent Inquiries** | Latest 5-10 inquiries with status badges and quick-view | 90% |\n| 3 | **Quick Actions** | \"Add Property\" button, \"View All Inquiries\" link | 80% |\n| 4 | **Properties Table** | Full CRUD list with search, filter, pagination | 100% |\n| 5 | **Property Create/Edit Form** | Multi-section form (photos, details, amenities, location) | 100% |\n| 6 | **Inquiries Table** | List with status filters (New, Read, Responded) | 100% |\n| 7 | **Inquiry Response View** | Message thread + reply form + status change | 80% |\n| 8 | **Users Table** | Renter list with status, activity, suspension toggle | 90% |\n| 9 | **Sidebar Navigation** | Collapsible sidebar with icons + labels | 100% |\n| 10 | **Top Bar** | Search, notifications, admin avatar dropdown | 90% |\n\n**Admin Dashboard Layout Convention:** Sidebar (200-250px) + Main Content Area. Stats cards in a horizontal row at top. Table or list below. \"Add New\" FAB or top-right button.\n\n### Property Detail Page\n\n**Standard Sections (present in 90%+ of competitors):**\n\n| # | Section | Content | Prevalence |\n|---|---------|---------|------------|\n| 1 | **Photo Gallery** | Hero image + thumbnail strip + \"View all photos\" link | 100% |\n| 2 | **Header** | Title, address, price, bed/bath/sqft summary | 100% |\n| 3 | **Description** | Free-text property description paragraph(s) | 100% |\n| 4 | **Amenities Grid** | Icon + label grid (2-4 columns) | 95% |\n| 5 | **Floor Plan** | Floor plan image with zoom capability | 60% |\n| 6 | **Property Details/Specs** | Table: Type, Year Built, Deposit, Lease Terms, Pets, Parking | 80% |\n| 7 | **Location Map** | Embedded Google Map with pin | 95% |\n| 8 | **Inquiry/Contact** | Form (name, email, phone, message) + \"Send\" CTA | 100% |\n| 9 | **Favorite Toggle** | Heart icon for saving/unsaving | 90% |\n| 10 | **Similar/Related Properties** | Card row of suggested properties nearby | 50% |\n\n**Layout Convention:** Two-column layout — Main content (70%) left, Sidebar (30%) right. Sidebar is typically sticky and contains the inquiry form or contact CTA. On mobile, stacks to single column; inquiry CTA becomes a sticky bottom bar. Photo gallery always at top, full-width.\n\n### Auth Pages (Login / Register)\n\n**Standard Patterns:**\n\n| # | Pattern | Details | Prevalence |\n|---|---------|---------|------------|\n| 1 | **Split-screen layout** | Left: brand/gradient, Right: form | 60% |\n| 2 | **Centered card layout** | Form in white card centered on colored background | 40% |\n| 3 | **Email + Password fields** | Full-width inputs, 48px height | 100% |\n| 4 | **Social login buttons** | Google, Apple, Facebook | 70% |\n| 5 | **\"Forgot Password\" link** | Below password field | 100% |\n| 6 | **\"Don't have an account? Sign up\"** | Below form | 100% |\n| 7 | **Password show/hide toggle** | Eye icon in password field right side | 70% |\n\n---\n\n## PRD Reference Analysis\n\n| PRD Feature | Reference Source | Dominant UI Pattern | NestFind Implication |\n|-------------|-----------------|---------------------|---------------------|\n| Property search with filters | Zillow, Apartments.com | Map+list split, filter panel, property cards | Implement card+filter pattern; map is nice-to-have for v1 |\n| Property detail with photo gallery | Zillow, Airbnb | Full-width hero image, thumbnail strip, sectioned content below | Photo-first design; gallery with thumbnails |\n| Google Maps integration | Zillow, Apartments.com | Embedded map section with pin on detail page; optionally on search | Detail page map is mandatory |\n| Favorites / Save properties | Zillow, Airbnb | Heart icon toggle; dedicated Saved/Favorites page | Heart toggle on cards + detail page; Favorites page |\n| Inquiry / Contact form | Zillow, Apartments.com | Sidebar form or modal; name, email, phone, message + Send CTA | Sidebar on detail page; confirmation toast |\n| Admin property management | Dashboard patterns on Behance/Dribbble | Sidebar + table + multi-section form; stats cards | Follow standard admin dashboard layout |\n| Admin inquiry management | Apartments.com Manager, Behance | Table with status badges (New/Read/Responded), inline reply | Table with status filters, reply view |\n| Admin user management | Dashboard patterns | Table with status (Active/Suspended) + action buttons | Model after Stripe-style user tables |\n| Renter registration | Zillow, Airbnb | \"Join\" / \"Sign Up\" — email, name, password, optional phone | Simple form; social login optional for v1 |\n\n---\n\n## Design Gap Analysis\n\n**What competitors do well:**\n- Photo-first, immersive browsing experience\n- Map integration as core discovery mechanism\n- Robust, responsive filter panels\n- Trust-building elements (verified listings, reviews, badges)\n\n**What competitors do poorly (opportunity for NestFind):**\n- Ad-heavy interfaces that clutter the browsing experience\n- Overly complex filter panels that overwhelm casual renters\n- Slow page loads due to heavy tracking scripts\n- Poor mobile inquiry/applications flow\n\n**NestFind differentiators to emphasize in design:**\n1. **Clean, ad-free browsing** — minimal, focused UI\n2. **Streamlined inquiry flow** — simple contact form, no multi-step applications\n3. **Quick favorites** — fast toggle without friction\n4. **Simple admin dashboard** — focused on essential management tasks, not bloated with upsells\n5. **Mobile-responsive as first principle** — not an afterthought\n\n---\n\n*End of Domain Research. Proceed to Phase 3: Design Guide generation.*\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude-project/nestfind/design/DOMAIN_RESEARCH.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":".claude-project/nestfind/design/DOMAIN_RESEARCH.md","time":{"start":1779178131299,"end":1779178131735}},"id":"prt_e3f451d7a0013VYdi5v7on0QlT","sessionID":"ses_1c0bd0875ffeDBfk5LNf5rH20A","messageID":"msg_e3f450b120017KOhWfnMJ27vkD"}}
